name: Groundfish Survey Invertebrate Data
description: The Irish Groundfish Surveys is part of an annual International Bottom Trawl Survey (IBTS) programme co-ordinated by the International Council for the Exploration of the Sea(ICES). The survey is carriedout over 47 daysbetween October-December each year by the MarineInstitute and collectsdemersal trawl and ancillarydata in Irish watersto produce relative abundance indicesfor fisheries management in the NorthwestAtlantic Shelf waters.
